Current Config ```bash # Check schema exists gateway config.schema.lookup agents.list.*.heartbeat.model # Check current value gateway config.get agents.list[0].heartbeat ``` If no heartbeat section exists, the heartbeat uses the agent's primary model. ### Step 2: Edit Config File Directly

On Windows, use Node.js to avoid PowerShell variable stripping:

```javascript
// Edit openclaw.json directly
const fs = require('fs');
const path = require('path');
const configPath = path.join(process.env.USERPROFILE, '.openclaw', 'openclaw.json');

const config = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(configPath, 'utf8'));

// Add heartbeat model if not present
if (!config.agents.list[0].heartbeat) {
    config.agents.list[0].heartbeat = {};
}
config.agents.list[0].heartbeat.model = 'nvidia/nemotron-3-ultra-550b-a55b:free';

fs.writeFileSync(configPath, JSON.stringify(config, null, 2), 'utf8');
console.log('heartbeat.model set');
```

Or via PowerShell (careful with variable expansion):

```powershell
node -e @"
const fs=require('fs');
const p=require('path').join(process.env.USERPROFILE,'.openclaw','openclaw.json');
const c=JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(p,'utf8'));
if(!c.agents.list[0].heartbeat)c.agents.list[0].heartbeat={};
c.agents.list[0].heartbeat.model='nvidia/nemotron-3-ultra-550b-a55b:free';
fs.writeFileSync(p,JSON.stringify(c,null,2),'utf8');
console.log('Done');
"@
```

### Step 3: Restart Gateway

```bash
gateway restart --reason "heartbeat model change" --note "heartbeat.model set to nemotron-ultra"
```

**Important**: On Windows, always use `gateway restart`, never `pm2 stop/start` or create Windows Scheduled Tasks (causes Telegram getUpdates collisions).
